  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed. The model risk level is 3, decision consequence is Medium, and model influence is Medium, yielding a required credibility level commensurate with Medium assurance. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed their required levels; the Test conditions factor falls one gradation short of the required level due to testing being performed under a single load condition. Despite this shortfall, the assessment team determined that the breadth of experimental replication across two independent laboratories and the conservative acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96, QoI difference < 10%) provide sufficient compensating evidence to support a Medium assurance declaration and an Accepted decision outcome.",
  "couName": "Non-cannulated F1717 compression-bending",
  "decision": "Accepted",
