      "rationale": "Three mesh refinement levels were evaluated (coarse ~180k elements, medium ~420k elements, fine ~910k elements). QoI change between medium and fine was 0.9% for stiffness and 1.3% for yield force. Richardson extrapolation confirmed GCI < 1.5%. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver convergence criteria documented; force and displacement residuals < 1e-4. Required level 2.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear static analyses used Newton-Raphson iteration with force residual tolerance 1e-5 and displacement residual tolerance 1e-5. All load steps converged without bisection beyond the first increment. Achieved level 2 meets required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation protocol with independent peer review of model setup. Required level 2.",
      "rationale": "A simulation execution plan (SEP) was prepared prior to analysis. An independent analyst reviewed boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions against the SEP. One discrepancy (incorrect friction coefficient on screw-vertebra interface) was identified and corrected before results were extracted. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification of constitutive model choices and contact formulation relative to physical phenomena. Required level 2.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) represented by bilinear isotropic hardening with parameters from ASTM-certified coupon testing. UHMWPE vertebral body surrogate represented by elastic-plastic model calibrated to manufacturer data sheets. Augmented Lagrange contact formulation selected to capture screw-rod interface slip. Literature review confirmed model form choices are consistent with published pedicle screw FEA studies. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material and geometric inputs traceable to measurements or certified material data. Required level 2.",
      "rationale": "Geometry imported from production CAD files (GD&T-controlled). Material properties sourced from ASTM-certified tensile test coupons (n=5 per lot). Friction coefficients determined from pin-on-disk tribometry. Sensitivity analysis on ±10% material property variation showed <3% QoI change. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples representative of production geometry and material; traceability documented. Required level 2.",
      "rationale": "Eleven constructs assembled from production-released components with full lot traceability. Dimensional inspection confirmed components within drawing tolerances. Two laboratories used identical component lots to eliminate inter-lot variability as a confound. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of loading scenarios relevant to the COU, including at least two distinct load magnitudes or configurations. Required level 3 given model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending load configuration at a single displacement rate (5 mm/min). While the protocol is standardized and reproducible, only one load condition was evaluated. The required level for this factor, given the model risk level of 3, is gradation 3; however, the single-condition test program achieves only gradation 2. This shortfall was noted in the assessment record. The assessment team judged that the strong cross-laboratory agreement (inter-lab CV 3.1%) and the conservative acceptance bounds partially compensate, but the factor does not formally meet the required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation inputs matched to experimental conditions with documented mapping. Required level 2.",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions in the FEA model were derived directly from the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry. Displacement rate was mapped to quasi-static assumption (confirmed by kinetic energy ratio < 1% of internal energy). Screw insertion torque was measured per construct and used to set pretension in the model. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of simulation and experimental QoIs using a pre-specified metric (E/uval). Required level 2.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) compared using ASME V&V 40 validation metric E/uval. All three QoIs: E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10%. Pre-registration of acceptance criteria prior to unblinding confirmed no post-hoc adjustment. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to the clinical failure mode (construct fracture/loosening) and regulatory submission claims. Required level 2.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly referenced in the 510(k) substantial equivalence argument. Each QoI maps to a distinct failure mode: stiffness to micromotion-induced pseudarthrosis, yield force to permanent deformation, and force at 40 mm to catastrophic fracture. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario matches the COU geometry, material, and loading to a documented degree. Required level 2.",
      "rationale": "Validation constructs used production-released non-cannulated 7.5 mm screws, the identical design evaluated in the COU. The ASTM F1717 loading scenario is the regulatory standard for this device class. No surrogate geometry or scaled model was employed. The validation scenario is judged highly relevant to the COU. Achieved level 3."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou1-noncannulated-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team reviewed all 13 V&V 40 credibility factors. Twelve factors meet or exceed their required levels. One factor — Test conditions — achieves gradation 2 against a required gradation of 3, reflecting the single-condition ASTM F1717 test program. The team determined that the strong cross-laboratory reproducibility (inter-lab CV 3.1%, N=11 constructs), conservative pre-specified acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96, QoI difference < 10%), and full traceability of inputs to production-certified components collectively provide sufficient compensating evidence to support a Medium assurance level and an Accepted decision for this COU. The shortfall in Test conditions is documented and flagged for remediation in subsequent design iterations.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
